    <note>Ren(1) Bozhuan [19194] CBD and Sichuan TZ, 122.16b have him hearning the jinshi in 1049 and identify him as a Shehong resident. Zhou(1) Bida [7197], in his funerary inscription for Bozhuang's great grandson, Xu [19200], identifies the family as Zixian (modern Santai) county residents and dates Bozhuan's jinshi in 1038. I am accepting CBD and Sichuan TZ for jinshi date, but leaving Bozhuan as a Zixian county resident, address of his ancestors and of his descendants. Zhou(1) Bida provides a list of his immediate ancestors: Chun's [19193] son was Taofu [24474] who begat Chonggao [24475], who begat Qi [24476], who begat Zhongjian [24477], who begat Bozhuan. CBD, 1, 661.</note>
